<item>
            <title>[LUCENE-1665] Remove SortField.AUTO</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/LUCENE-1665</link>
                <project id="12310110" key="LUCENE">Lucene - Core</project>
                        <description>&lt;p&gt;I&apos;d like to remove SortField.AUTO... it&apos;s dangerous for Lucene to&lt;br/&gt;
guess the type of your field, based on the first term it encounters.&lt;br/&gt;
It can easily be wrong, and, whether it&apos;s wrong or right could&lt;br/&gt;
suddenly change as you index different documents.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;It unexepctedly binds SortField to needing an IndexReader to do the&lt;br/&gt;
guessing.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;It&apos;s caused various problems in the past (most recently, for me on&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/LUCENE-1656&quot; title=&quot;When sorting by field, IndexSearcher should not compute scores by default&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;LUCENE-1656&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;) as we fix other issues/make improvements.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I&apos;d prefer that users of Lucene&apos;s field sort be explicit about the&lt;br/&gt;
type that Lucene should cast the field to.  Someday, if we have&lt;br/&gt;
optional strong&lt;span class=&quot;error&quot;&gt;&amp;#91;er&amp;#93;&lt;/span&gt; typing of Lucene&apos;s fields, such type information&lt;br/&gt;
would already be known.  But in the meantime, I think users should be&lt;br/&gt;
explicit.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
